I don't write a lot of reviews, so the fact that I'm taking the time to write this one should mean something to those who are willing to read it. I absolutely LOVE this bar! The whole aesthetic of the bar is very beautiful, the ambiance of it is truly peaceful and chill, but the main focus of the bar/restaurant is of course their drinks and food. Honestly, I've been to almost every single bar on 18th Street and I can say that no other bar's cocktails are as good as the ones that are served here. The bartenders Juan and Adrianna are super sweet, friendly, and just great workers who know exactly how to make you feel at home. I love this bar so much that I have become a regular here, as soon as I walk thru the door, Juan (the bartender) greets me by name and already knows what I'm going to order and serves it to me before I could respond. I truly love this place and I recommend it to everyone looking for a simple, chill place to unwind and have a great drink.

I used to really dig this place. The margaritas were outstanding. But then they went months with no liquor license and one of the main things that drew me to this place was gone. I figured I should give it another shot. So my girlfriend and I made our way over there on a Sunday evening. We arrive at 10:15pm on Sunday, open the door, and walk in. The place is a ghost town. There's a couple at the table closest to the door and a lady sitting behind them tells me and my girlfriend that they are closed. I wondered how they were closed when their hours on Google said they closed at 11pm. Perhaps Google made a mistake? I didn't know. Then we left and curiosity got the better of us. We turned around and looked at the hours posted on the door.  The large sign showed that they close on Sundays at 11pm.  Checked Google again. Closing time on Sunday is posted as 11pm.  Checked Yelp. 11pm.  So, I can't help but feel a tad miffed and disappointed. All signs show me that the restaurant should've been open for another 45 minutes and that my girlfriend and I should have been able to enjoy the drink that we set out on purchasing. Instead, I type this from another bar that actually is open during the hours that are posted on their door. Crazy idea, right?  In order to avoid this type of confusion in the future, i've decided to simply patronize any of the other establishments in Pilsen. No hard feelings.

Have we all not been eating beef our whole lives?! She could've simply said they were out and I would've ordered something else. Instead, they chose to be shady, and I will not be returning. Plenty of other places out there that respect their patrons. Peace.

So the sorry behind this is that the last time I went there with a friend from out of town, I had to send a drink back but we were never checked on for a solid 20 minutes which is when I flagged someone over, which I hate doing. So then apparently the manager, who we found out is also the owner, came over, thinking she was coming over to apologize that no one checked on us for so long, but instead she was incredibly disrespectful and scolded me like a child because "I waited so long," which she wouldn't let me explain why (which was that no waiter came over to check on us and I had to wave someone over to get their attention), she would just in interrupt me. Mind you, we had THREE servers that night because things were slow, and not ONE of them came to check on us after we tried our food. We will never go back again because of the poor experience. Definitely not worth the price.  I've been here three times. The first time was very good. Not great but good but I want sure if the price was right. There's enough burger places with the exact same burgers that you can shop around. But they had nice paintings.  So, second try was also good. I got the Parmesan fries. It said truffle oil on the menu, but I guess I took for granted that they wouldn't use it like salt; I was wrong, and those fries didn't come off the bill but the truffle oil came out through my pores for days. And no, the chef doesn't think it's too much and no you can't just have Parmesan fries next time because it's all together.  Gave it a final go. Apparently kobe beef looks like tartar when it's medium rare. It wasn't good in any case (the ketchup style sauce was), and my partner's drink wasn't either (that did come off the bill).  I don't quibble about bills normally; you try it, maybe you don't like it, provide feedback, but suck it up because you ordered it. But when you provide feedback and then you're told that you're wrong, that's when you don't suck it up.  I know that if they read this review they'll say they're glad and they don't want my business anyway, and I know that because they told us as much when we provided feedback.

Nice little patio. Good brunch cocktails and nachos.

On a recent visit to the Pilsen neighborhood to attend First Friday Art Walk, we stumbled upon this restaurant  It was awesome. We had   shrimp tacos and a brussel sprouts side.  It had just enough spice to make it interesting.  I would definitely go back.
Food is amazing and service is even better. One of the only restaurants we could find in Pilsen that let a large group split checks as well.
The only place in Pilsen that will split checks. We had impeccable service and ended up going there for lunch and dinner in the same day.
I loved the water

Had a superb time, our waitress offered to help with specials and beer selection.  They have super good selection of beers...  the burgers are    the best i have had in a few time...   we all had a perfect night.
Brunch is spot on, with great specials any day.
(Translated by Google) Excellent I love this place 100% recommended  (Original) Excelente me encanta este lugar 100% recomendado
Located in the lower floor, great staff and food options! The only thing negative is poor cell phone reception, phone your party beforehand.
locally sourced food that tastes delicious everytime
The food here is really great. I'd suggest getting a Tamarind Margarita.
The drink selection is one of the best I've seen for a restaurant and the food is inventive and delicious. The atmosphere is comfortable and the staff is very kind and eager.
Great Food, awesome atmosphere! Highly recommend.
Delicious food, great selection of beers and a great staff! The art on the walls are local artists and a good combination of mexican american food. Cant wait to go back!

Named after a town in the former Czechoslovakia, this place is a must in Pilsen.  Great brunch spot.  First of all they have unlimited mimosa with meals for $25.  I think it is Sunday only though.  Might want to check that.  The place is a cool half basement with a small patio.  Tons of cool art on the walls with other murals spread around the space.  I've eaten here about 3 times and each meal I've had was great.  It's a little Mexican with a twist of gentrification.  So it you hate that word, maybe you may want to chose a different place.  But for us who want a cool atmosphere and solid meal, this a great choice in Pilsen.
Great food, fine atmosphere, good service..Highly recommend..

Awesome gastropub with great Latino influenced bar- fare, and truly amazing cocktails. The tequila and mezcal selection is top notch, and service is always Excelente. Definitely one of the MUST visit places when you come to Pilsen.

The Pl-zen Tuesday burger & beer combo is one of the best deals in Chicago. The food is incredibly high quality and very reasonably priced. We go to Pl-zen pretty regularly between the Tuesday burger and the weekend bottomless brunch. The flavors are always balanced and interesting, add in the eclectic vibe and semi-hidden stairway entrance, and you will find that each visit to Pl-zen feels like a retreat.  To end the meal on a high note, try the donuts. They are crisp, decadent perfection!

Had my brithday brunch there...and everything  was great!  Adriana was very accomodating...she went through the menu and beer selections...it was a very good experience. Went  back a few weeks later and needed to make some adjustments to my cocktail order for medical reasons  can't have sugary stuff talked to the waiter and he communicated that to the bartender and they made me a great margarita! They really go above and beyond with the sevice! The food is excellent!!! Definitely  a must try!
Great spot, but can get quite noisy. Sit on patio, if possible.

Great Restaurant - a real gem!  It doesn't look like much from the outside but you ought to try this restaurant.  It's beautiful inside and the chef is very good.  As good or better than the brunches you find at restaurants in Lincoln Park or Wrigleyville.  I was tempted to take a photo of our meals and I'm hardly ever inclined to do that.  A lot of effort and thought goes into the food and it's only about $10.00/dish.  I'll definitely go back!
Good!

Pl-zen burger was fantastic! First time eating bison. 😏 Sweet potato fries were great, but too much like a dessert (dipped in cinnamon sugar) to really be paired with the burger, in my opinion- would have preferred them on their own. Overall, very good experience, would definitely go back and have already recommended.

Favorite place to grub in Chicago!  Always a treat.  Great artsy & chill atmosphere, awesome service.  Best turkey burger on pretzel bun I've EVER had! !! The drinks and alcohol are perfect. --wide selection.  Oooh, and brunch with bottomless mimosas on Saturdays are epic!
Amazing chilaquilles, fantastic bloody mary, and super friendly staff.

I came here with a couple of friends and let me say their beer selection is top notch; or at least thats what my friends tell me (I'm not a big beer drinker). I had a great time, there was a great vibe and some good people and their appetizers are quite tasty.

We had high hopes for this place as it's been on my radar for awhile, however it let me down mostly due to service.  The service was extremely slow.  It took forever to get our server to come back to us to order drinks.  I just ordered one before I was finished because I knew it would take about 20 minutes to get it. The bartenders are slow as well.  I'm not sure why - its not that big of a place.   The food was ok - I think they charge too much for what they are offering.  Don't think we will be back.

Pl-Zen really stands out whether you are driving past it or walking.  That's exactly how I found out about this place, and I had to look it up as soon as I stopped driving my car.  The restaurant space is in the basement, which did surprise me.  Checking it out online gave me the impression it would be on the first floor of the 2 story octopus building. The interior is very casual yet clean with exposed brick walls, and Pl-Zen caters to the artistic hipsters in the neighborhood.  Local artist's works are showcased on the walls. The food was great and not too expensive.  I ordered the Diablo, which had just the right amount of kick! So good!

I'm a fan! From dinner to brunch you really cannot go wrong. I always make friends try the bone marrow because its done so uniquely here it takes away the normal fear that people have. Also, bottomless mimosa brunch perfect! Who doesn't love a bottomless mimosa while you're enjoying your brunch and catching up with good friends.

Usual choice for great brews, cocktails and food. Love that the menu changes (even if it means missing old favorites) seasonally. Cesar appreciates all of the customers & you will feel very special, indeed as a 'regular'. :)

LOOK Great eclectic decor in an urban basement setting, visited during winter but has some outdoor seating that may be nice FEEL Laid back atmosphere with soft lighting; two person tables slightly cramped but there is the option to combine tables. Many options for seating SMILES Friendly and professional service DRINKS Great beer list, but only a few on tap -- the tap beers we tried were fantastic. BELLY Delicious and hot food -- we had the Mac and cheese in a skillet and the portabella mushroom burger; great options for vegitarians CLEAN Bathrooms were kind of old and didnt go with the feel of the place, but still clean and not deterring.

The place is very cute and trendy! Our server was very nice. We were the first to get seated and the last to get our food. I thought it was odd that everyone around us was getting their food before us as we were the first to put our order in. Our waiter recognized the wait and comped one of our drinks.   45min after ordering our dishes finally came out. I ordered the braised beef with the side of risotto.But instead of the risotto what came out was the mash potato. I was disappointed because the waiter was raving about how delicious the side of risotto was and out came mash potato. The price point of the menu is pretty pricey for the area. Despite the wait, overall the food was good. I would give this place another chance for redemption.

I love hanging out at Pl-zen, a great new bar in Pilsen.  The beer selection is killer, and the food is unique and delicious.  The atmosphere is chill and relaxed with a beautiful interior.  Wood finishes are a nice touch!  I love that one of the servers recognizes me each time I come in, even if a week or two goes by!

An excellent gastro-pub in Pilsen.  Perfect date spot!  Love it.  The service is tops.  The staff remembers your name.  Antimosa is a delicious beer/mimosa.  Shredded beef eggs benedict was a little heavy, but nice.

One of Pilsen neighborhood hidden gems.  Great beer and drink selection.  Great menu with a variety of dishes to meet your needs.  Great place to start the evening or have a first date.  Trust me, I have done both!
Great fries! great burger down the street from where i live of the 18th stop on the pink line
Absolutely Amazing?!!!
